{
  "texts": [
    "This suggests that the complexity of current datasets may be insufficient to distinguish between different models significantly.",
    "Therefore, we need to construct more challenging datasets containing richer structural information and temporal evolution patterns to evaluate models' modeling capabilities better.",
    "• Secondly, operations like users unfollowing others are shared in real applications, but currently, there is a lack of real-world datasets containing such edge deletion data.",
    "Expanding datasets could involve collecting and integrating data with real edge deletion operations to simulate the dynamics of graph data in the real world.",
    "This can help assess models' robustness and performance when handling edge deletion."
  ]
}